# Documentation

- **In-code:** Comment only when the “why” or contract is not obvious. No restating the code. No long-lived TODOs without a clear next step or owner.
- **Repo docs:** `docs/` is source of truth for product and architecture. Update `docs/architecture.md` when stack or high-level design changes; update `docs/product-spec.md` when scope or constraints change. Keep README aligned with run instructions and MVP scope.
- **Tone:** Factual. No marketing speak, no “awesome” or “simple but powerful”.
- **Rule files and commit-convention:** Treat as binding. When editing them, keep them strict and practical; do not add generic advice or dilute.
